  <prompt>
    Per FR-18: if stored envelope is stale (>1 hour) or absent, fire-and-forget POST to `/api/insights/ask`. UI must not block (NFR-03). Per FR-19, the existing stale envelope renders immediately while background invocation runs.
  </prompt>

  <role>Form async-invocation developer.</role>

  <goal>
    OnLoad handler triggers async POST without awaiting; existing envelope rendered immediately; no spinner; no blocking.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="handler">Task 040 output</file>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-widgets-r1/spec.md (FR-18, FR-19)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec-FR-18">Fire-and-forget — do NOT await</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-03">Form TTI unaffected</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>fetch fire-and-forget, xrm.webapi.online.execute</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-widgets-r1/spec.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Compose POST body">topic, mode, subject, parameters</step>
    <step order="2" name="fetch() without await">Or Xrm.WebApi.online.execute analog</step>
    <step order="3" name="Catch promise rejection">Log only; do not surface to user</step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify no blocking">Form TTI metric</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">insightWidgetOnLoad.ts (pre-warm logic added)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">POST fires when envelope stale or absent</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">POST does NOT block form TTI</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Promise rejection only logged, never surfaced</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Completed 2026-06-11. `_firePrewarm` body replaced with `fetch('/api/insights/ask', { ... })` invocation. POST body: `{ topic: 'matter-health', mode: 'single', subject: 'matter:{guid}', parameters: {} }`. Detached Promise via `pending.then(onFulfilled, onRejected).catch(...)` — no `await`, double-layered swallow ensures no "Uncaught (in promise)" runtime warnings. Fresh-envelope path returns early (no POST). Create-mode (no record id) returns early. Synchronous failures + async rejections both `console.warn` only — never surfaced to user. `_version` bumped 0.1.0 → 0.2.0. tsc clean (TypeScript 5.9.2). Compiled .js emitted alongside .ts.
  </notes>
</task>
